eturn 2\nmyCalendarThree.book(5, 15); // return 3\nmyCalendarThree.book(5, 10); // return 3\nmyCalendarThree.book(25, 55); // return 3\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= startTime < endTime <= 10⁹`\n\n- At most `400` calls will be made to `book`.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/my-calendar-iii/","problemName":"My Calendar III","problemNumber":732,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"A `k`-booking happens when `k` events have some non-empty intersection (i.e., there is some time that is common to all `k` events.)\n\nYou are given some events `[startTime, endTime)`, after each given event, return an integer `k` representing the maximum `k`-booking between all the previous events.\n\nImplement the `MyCalendarThree` class:\n\n- `MyCalendarThree()` Initializes the object.\n\n- `int book(int startTime, int endTime)` Returns an integer `k` representing the largest integer such that there exists a `k`-booking in the calendar.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input\n[\"MyCalendarThree\", \"book\", \"book\", \"book\", \"book\", \"book\", \"book\"]\n[[], [10, 20], [50, 60], [10, 40], [5, 15], [5, 10], [25, 55]]\nOutput\n[null, 1, 1, 2, 3, 3, 3]\n\nExplanation\nMyCalendarThree myCalendarThree = new MyCalendarThree();\nmyCalendarThree.book(10, 20); // return 1\nmyCalendarThree.book(50, 60); // return 1\nmyCalendarThree.book(10, 40); // return 2\nmyCalendarThree.book(5, 15); // return 3\nmyCalendarThree.book(5, 10); // return 3\nmyCalendarThree.book(25, 55); // return 3","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `0 <= startTime < endTime <= 10⁹`\n\n- At most `400` calls will be made to `book`.","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Hard","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"A `k`-booking happens when `k` events have some non-empty intersection (i.e., there is some time that is common t