raintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a network of `n` nodes, labeled from `1` to `n`. You are also given `times`, a list of travel times as directed edges `times[i] = (ui, vi, wi)`, where `ui` is the source node, `vi` is the target node, and `wi` is the time it takes for a signal to travel from source to target.\n\nWe will send a signal from a given node `k`. Return *the **minimum** time it takes for all the* `n` *nodes to receive the signal*. If it is impossible for all the `n` nodes to receive the signal, return `-1`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/0743-network-delay-time/743-931_example_1.png","sequence":1,"sha256":"23518f812fc455d4fb5f2224b68e4d4f5fb84347e0963ee636efc582690c2496","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: times = [[2,1,1],[2,3,1],[3,4,1]], n = 4, k = 2\nOutput: 2","type":"code"},{"sequence":3,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":4,"text":"Input: times = [[1,2,1]], n = 2, k = 1\nOutput: 1","type":"code"},{"sequence":5,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":6,"text":"Input: times = [[1,2,1]], n = 2, k = 2\nOutput: -1","type":"code"},{"sequence":7,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= k <= n <= 100`\n\n- `1 <= times.length <= 6000`\n\n- `times[i].length == 3`\n\n- `1 <= ui, vi <= n`\n\n- `ui != vi`\n\n- `0 <= wi <= 100`\n\n- All the pairs `(ui, vi)` are **unique**. (i.e., no multiple edges.)","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Depth-First Search","Breadth-First Search","Graph Theory","Heap (Priority Queue)","Shortest Path"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a network of `n` nodes, labeled from `1` to `n`. You are also given `times`, a list of travel times as directed edges `times[i] = (ui, vi, wi)`, where `ui` is the source node, `vi` is the target node, and `wi` is the time it takes for a signal to tr