ated at (1, 0) and (0, 3) cannot catch up with you.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: ghosts = [[1,0]], target = [2,0]\nOutput: false\nExplanation: You need to reach the destination (2, 0), but the ghost at (1, 0) lies between you and the destination.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: ghosts = [[2,0]], target = [1,0]\nOutput: false\nExplanation: The ghost can reach the target at the same time as you.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= ghosts.length <= 100`\n\n- `ghosts[i].length == 2`\n\n- `-10⁴ <= xi, yi <= 10⁴`\n\n- There can be **multiple ghosts** in the same location.\n\n- `target.length == 2`\n\n- `-10⁴ <= xtarget, ytarget <= 10⁴`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Math"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are playing a simplified PAC-MAN game on an infinite 2-D grid. You start at the point `[0, 0]`, and you are given a destination point `target = [xtarget, ytarget]` that you are trying to get to. There are several ghosts on the map with their starting positions given as a 2D array `ghosts`, where `ghosts[i] = [xi, yi]` represents the starting position of the `i^(th)` ghost. All inputs are **integral coordinates**.\n\nEach turn, you and all the ghosts may independently choose to either **move 1 unit** in any of the four cardinal directions: north, east, south, or west, or **stay still**. All actions happen **simultaneously**.\n\nYou escape if and only if you can reach the target **before** any ghost reaches you. If you reach any square (including the target) at the **same time** as a ghost, it **does not** count as an escape.\n\nReturn `true`* if it is possible to escape regardless of how the ghosts move, otherwise return *`false`*.*\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: ghosts = [[1,0],[0,3]], target = [0,1]\nOutput: tr